title: People Are My Favorite Thing
extra:
"It’s glorious. It’s wonderful. It’s warm. It’s funky. It’s the balls…."

It's Ankit Love and his debut alternative funk album "Forever." realesed in November 2011 on iTunes. It's has already earned Love a No.1 hit on the MTV Hive top 100 chart with the sci-fi music video "Beethoven Burst" which was also featured on VH1 "Fresh new Music: January 2012" Two singles from the album were in the FMQB Radio Charts top 200 simultaneously, and "Beethoven Burst" went on to be a Top 40 hit, reaching number 28. The album was played also played on over 130 college radio stations at the end of last year throughout the USA including WGTB in Washington DC, WNSU in Ft Lauderdale, WIIT in Chicago, WECB in Boston, KLSU in St. Louis, WXIN in Providence, RI and WPPJ in Pittsburgh.

Stuart Mason of Aberdeen Student Radio describes Love as a highly unique individual with an unique take on music and the world. With track titles such as ‘Spill The Milky Way’, ‘Lightning Lady’, ‘Mental Revolution’ and ‘Unite+Funk’, you realise that this is a special guy making special music. And when you delve that bit deeper and look at some of his lyrics, you can really see that this is a man who marches to his own funky, sexy beat." And he hails Love's debut album Forever as a "totally unique and utterly brilliant release, mixing the spirituality of India with the sunshine of California, a musical tour de force that melds funk, soul, rock, hip hop and others into a groundbreaking record that will stay with you long after you’ve turned it off. One of the albums of the year. Amazing."


He states that "the masterpiece of the album however is the stunning, breathtakingly awesome ‘Beethoven Burst’. It is quite simply amazing. There’s no other word to describe this beautiful, sexy, funking tune. You just have to give it a listen or better yet head over to Youtube and check out the stupendous video, created and directed by Ankit Love himself."

Andy Gesner top indie music video promoter explains that 'Beethoven Burst' "finds Love cast as an interplanetary space commander in search for the cosmic holy grail, with a crew of hot (and barely clothed) bombshells at the controls. The video mixes ideas of faith, imagination, love, Star Trek, and The Sistine Chapel all into one Hollywood movie-like production that anyone with a pair of eyes and ears will definitely not want to miss." He states "after witnessing this bizarre, yet completely awe-inspiring spectacle, we are certain that Love could be our generation’s Ziggy Stardust."

In February 2012 he also released a special on-line cover single of the popular Indian track "Why this Kolaveri Di." His version of the song was shared by several celerities on Twitter including three Bollywood film stars.

title: Ophelia - Take Me To The River
Picture Perfect
extra:
PICTURE PERFECT

V1:
perfect pictures, shiny frames
no one here to take the blame
no one can recall the names
smiling faces, all the same

and

V2:
colored boxes, silken bows
feathered hats, and polished toes
blooming flowers, lovely scents
ignore the bills, don't pay the rent

CH:
it was all a perfect waste
held together with pins and paste
nothing was ever out of place
so many pretty things to take up space
it was all a perfect --

(waste?)
V3:
You looked so much better then.
Wanted by so many men.
Pale blue eyes and perfect smile.
Unread letters in a pile.

it was all a perfect waste
held together with pins and paste
nothing was ever out of place

She Don't Know It
extra:
Cornel Dyke is a Country singer/songwriter who currently resides in Aldergrove BC, Canada. Cornel, his wife Bonnita and some of his six children, have showcased their original music at small local venues and festivals including McBurney’s Coffee House, Abbotsford Agrifair and the popular Merritt Mountain Music Festival.

Cornel was raised in a musical family. Singsongs were regular events whenever relatives and friends got together. Cornel’s country roots can be traced to his country-singing father Hank Dyke. Hank was well known in the fifties, playing with the likes of Elmer Tippe and Loretta Lynn. Cornel can also credit his artist mother for much of his creative ability.

In the eighties while living in the interior of British Columbia, Cornel played in a family band with his dad and brothers. Their band became a popular local band placing first in two “Battle of the Bands”. After winning a day in a local recording studio, Cornel was successful in having four original songs play-listed in 3 local radio stations. After moving to the BC Lower Mainland, Cornel did very little with his music for several years.

In 2000 with the encouragement of his wife Bonnita, Cornel decided to once again become active with his music. He joined the BCSSA to showcase his original songs and he attended local NSAI (Nashville Songwriter’s Association International) songwriting workshops to learn how to write better ones.

Cornel’s efforts began paying off! Cornel was awarded “2004 Songwriter of the year” and “2004 Song of the year” for the Bruce Kilby co-write, “It’s Really Comin’ Down”, by the BCSSA. Cornel’s first single, “She Don’t Know It” written with brother Kevin Dyke received radio airplay worldwide. In 2005 it also reached the semifinals for the ISC (International Song Contest) Country category. That year there were over 11,000 entries from both professional and amateur songwriters. Cornel’s debut CD titled “Here I Am” was released in 2005. It received great reviews as well as a nomination for “Album of the year” by the British Columbia Country Music Association.

Cornel has had a dormant stage with his music since 2006 but now that his children including Tallya, have taken an interest in creating music, Cornel has decided to once again pursue his love of songwriting. So keep your ears tuned for more original music from Cornel and his family!

In 2000 with the encouragement of his wife Bonnita, Cornel decided to once again become active with his music. He joined the BCSSA to showcase his original songs and he attended local NSAI (Nashville Songwriter’s Association International) songwriting workshops to learn how to write better ones.

Cornel’s efforts began paying off! Cornel was awarded “2004 Songwriter of the year” and “2004 Song of the year” for the Bruce Kilby co-write, “It’s Really Comin’ Down”, by the BCSSA. Cornel’s first single, “She Don’t Know It” written with brother Kevin Dyke received radio airplay worldwide. In 2005 it also reached the semifinals for the ISC (International Song Contest) Country category. That year there were over 11,000 entries from both professional and amateur songwriters. Cornel’s debut CD titled “Here I Am” was released in 2005. It received great reviews as well as a nomination for “Album of the year” by the British Columbia Country Music Association.

Cornel has had a dormant stage with his music since 2006 but now that his children including Tallya, have taken an interest in creating music, Cornel has decided to once again pursue his love of songwriting. So keep your ears tuned for more original music from Cornel and his family!

title: Heroes and Cowards
extra: Mellow Head is a three piece band consisting of Forrest Jones, Rob Rangel and Luke McDowell. They started playing together in 2010 when Forrest Jones asked Rob and Luke to work with him on some home recordings of songs he had composed. The chemistry as a band was apparent immediately, despite the vast difference in ages and musical interests. Forrest, at the time a fifteen year old who had written his first songs as early as thirteen, was heavily influenced by Green Day and other pop punk artists, while Rob, a drummer in his fifties and a thirty year veteran of the sticks and skins, had roots in jazz and classic rock. Add to the mix, Luke McDowell, a fifteen year veteran bass player in his thirties who's area of music included heavier sounds like Metallica and Nirvana, but who's love of the bass required the proficiency of such bass legends as John Entwhistle of The Who, Geddy Lee of Rush and the incomparable Les Claypool of Primus. Together, fusing the styles, Mellow Head formed a new genre of music, dubbed "Modern Retro", which defines their obvious modern and classic influences. Their love for music (not genres) explains why on their debut album, "Heroes and Cowards" you will be lulled by the haunting melodies of such songs as Memories and Secrets and Why but then shocked into the awakening by songs like Shadows of the World and STRIKE (Keep the Fire Lit), or moved to tap your toes to the eclectic bass riffs of songs like What's Next. Check out their debut album by visiting amazon.com or iTunes where the album Heroes and Cowards can be purchased

Add to the mix, Luke McDowell, a fifteen year veteran bass player in his thirties who's area of music included heavier sounds like Metallica and Nirvana, but who's love of the bass required the proficiency of such bass legends as John Entwhistle of The Who, Geddy Lee of Rush and the incomparable Les Claypool of Primus. Together, fusing the styles, Mellow Head formed a new genre of music, dubbed "Modern Retro", which defines their obvious modern and classic influences. Their love for music (not genres) explains why on their debut album, "Heroes and Cowards" you will be lulled by the haunting melodies of such songs as Memories and Secrets and Why but then shocked into the awakening by songs like Shadows of the World and STRIKE (Keep the Fire Lit), or moved to tap your toes to the eclectic bass riffs of songs like What's Next. Check out their debut album by visiting amazon.com or iTunes where the album Heroes and Cowards can be purchased

title: 01 City One
extra:
The moment of (re)union a young woman with her brother, for whom she has been looking for a long time throughout the vastness of space. At it's core, the Horizon Venture is a story of how a child's fragile love can survive the coldness of time and space, men and machines, and go on to change the destinies of stars.

KEYS: Chris Jerome
BASS: Vidal Montgomery

title: 02 Black Waters
extra:
A lament for the unborn child, an ode to the power of flexibility in the face of adversity, and a requiem for the strength of collective experience, no matter how arduous or gruesome. A reminder that all things have their season, and every dog will have it's day in the sun.

VOCALS: Nanar Vorperian
KEYS: Zoe Rahman
BASS: Vidal Montgomery

title: 03 The Signal
extra:
An audible harmonic of the background noise that pollutes, infects and controls everyone's life, and the even deeper sound of silence and freedom which it compresses, but must invariably escape. This track focuses on the annoying consciousness of being conformed to forces which are detrimental. The literal meaning of "person" is "Per Sona" - that which is formed through sound. By extension, negative emotions are generated by negative frequencies, to which the the acoustic bass, drums and voice towards the end of the track bring an amount of relief.

VOCALS: Vidal Montgomery, Nanar Vorperian
DRUMS: Daniel Crosby
KEYS: Chris Jerome
VIOLAS: Natalie Scahill, Alistair Scahill
BASS: Vidal Montgomery

title: 04 The Cutoff
extra:
Decision: From the latin Decide meaning "to Cut off from" - a point of no return.
In the case of this civilisation, the cut off point being the decision to harness the power of the atom.
The middle section of the track attempts to intimate the joy and happiness that is promised on the other side of physical life. Often, where the caterpillar sees certain death, the master will see a butterfly in an embryonic state.

SAXOPHONE: Shabaka Hutchings
PERCUSSION: Donald Gamble
DRUMS: Daniel Crosby
KEYS: Chris Jerome
PIANO: Robert Mitchell
VIOLINS: Susan Collier,
VIOLAS: Natalie Scahill, Alistair Scahill
BASS: Vidal Montgomery

title: 05 Two
extra:
Music from the soundtrack to "The Horizon Venture" A tale of intergalactic diaspora told through spoken word, dance, video, visuals, and music for the UK live show tour, supported by Arts Council England and The Shrine

Inspired by the book "The Horizon Venture" by Vidal Montgomery

Album Release date:
RELEASE DATE 1st OCTOBER 2012
www.thehorizonventure.com

Recorded at Taylormade Studios and Holodeck Studios, London
Producer / programmer: Vidal Montgomery
Recording engineers: Steve Reece and Courtney Pine

for all enquiries contact Vidal Montgomery - info@thehorizonventure.com

1st Floor, Chocolate Factory 2
4 Coburg Road Wood Green
London N22 6UJ

title: 06 The Xienom
extra:
This track is about the other side of Xenophobia; the veneer of fear which masks the commonality of people looking to express their truth. As the ancient African proverb goes "until the lion tells his own tale, the story will always glorify the hunter". So this track is about how emotions, and our reactions to them, can induce sympathy or fear, and how aggression is often a mask for vulnerability

PERCUSSION: Donald Gamble
DRUMS: Daniel Crosby
KEYS: Chris Jerome
VIOLIN: Susan Collier
VIOLAS: Natalie Scahill, Alistair Scahill
CELLO: Jenny Adejayan
BASS: Vidal Montgomery

title: 07 Duel
extra:
In contrast to the wider scale fully manifest military conflict of of the later track "The Battle" This track emotes the psychic attack of anticipation of conflict between two individuals, represented by the Berimbau-style col legno, and then short, sporadic bursts of activity as well prepared offensive / defensive moves are played out against each other.

PERCUSSION: Donald Gamble
DRUMS: Daniel Crosby
PIANO: Robert Mitchell
BASS: Vidal Montgomery

title: 08 The Entertainment District
extra:
What starts as a regular night out goes a little too far, and without warning! But in the future, people will still want entertainment; in the last 400 years,Afro Pop culture has been the groove against which "civilisation" has played out; This track explores the line between distraction and destruction 40 years from now.


DRUMS:Robert Fordjour
KEYS: Robert Mitchell
BASS: Vidal Montgomery
EWI: Shabaka Hutchings

title: 09 The Battle
extra:
This track is about a soldier's-eye view of a large military conflict; the bass groove is the singular consideration of survival which is clung to in order to endure and be victorious in the midst of organised chaos.

KEYS: Robert Mitchell, Vidal Montgomery
DRUMS: Robert Fordjour
BASS: Vidal Montgomery
EWI: Shabaka Hutchings

title: 10 The Horizon Venture Theme
extra: A reprise of the main thematic elements consistent throughout the work.  The piano/ violin interplay on the introduction is to represent the fragility of the astronaut's predicament, who willingly, or otherwise, entrusts his life to engineers who have built a craft to withstand environments that can only be guessed at.

We've all learned how to hide

between us and the rest of our kind

I hid behind a blindfold
gulping brimstone and stunned
Medusa's hair was everywhere at once

title: Summertime
extra:
Diamond Dust is a new Independent act from Canada. They have been on tour across North America since July '11 in support of their self-titled debut album.

The tour has had many highlights including playing SXSW in Austin, TX, booking the Whisky a Go-Go in LA and a TRiP event in Santa Monica, for which one of their songs was chosen to a appear on a 14 song compilation that is being produced and sold to celebrate the event.

There have also been some astonishing reviews of the album coming in, notably from the Canadian Broadcasting Corporation's music director, who had the following to say about the release: “Jo St-Onge and Craig "Riffer" Hare, a.k.a. Diamond Dust, remind one of peak period Led Zeppelin in their ability to dish out both blistering, full-bore rock, and lively, foot-stomping folk. More importantly, the songs are strong enough to keep fans of either style of music consistently - and highly - engaged. A very impressive debut.” Diamond Dust’s refreshing, yet familiar take on rock n' roll has also been described as “groovy, catchy, foot-tapping and reminiscent of classic rock".

The band is currently on tour across the US until the end of May, 2012 with the goal of coming back to Canada in June to begin recording their second album and continue touring Canada and the States for the Summer of 2012.

The tour has had many highlights including playing SXSW in Austin, TX, booking the Whisky a Go-Go in LA and a TRiP event in Santa Monica, for which one of their songs was chosen to a appear on a 14 song compilation that is being produced and sold to celebrate the event.

There have also been some astonishing reviews of the album coming in, notably from the Canadian Broadcasting Corporation's music director, who had the following to say about the release: “Jo St-Onge and Craig "Riffer" Hare, a.k.a. Diamond Dust, remind one of peak period Led Zeppelin in their ability to dish out both blistering, full-bore rock, and lively, foot-stomping folk. More importantly, the songs are strong enough to keep fans of either style of music consistently - and highly - engaged. A very impressive debut.” Diamond Dust’s refreshing, yet familiar take on rock n' roll has also been described as “groovy, catchy, foot-tapping and reminiscent of classic rock".

The band is currently on tour across the US until the end of May, 2012 with the goal of coming back to Canada in June to begin recording their second album and continue touring Canada and the States for the Summer of 2012

title: Nadine
extra: Neon Blue is fronted by veteran musicians, brothers, Mark (Songwriter Socan) & Sean Doney. For the band, their best music is yet to be recorded. Their debut, self-titled album, produced on a small budget of their own money, held up well against releases by the major studios, appearing on Country music charts around the world. The singles "Katie", "One Lonely Night" and "Thank God For The Simple Man", have since been heard by millions of radio listeners. In 2012, the Doneys continue to work on new, original music and the funding for their followup cd project. Thay are actively seeking a recording deal, sale of original song rights or alternative financing arrangement. The guys continue to do what they enjoy the most, play live shows for fans across Ontario, Canada.

title: Rock The Boat
Take My Pain Away
extra:
Conceit has something to prove! This is more than obvious when you get the chance to see him perform. The energy and passion he displays on stage is only complimented by the creativity and appeal of his music. During a time when hip hop has either gotten to preachy or much too ignorant, Conceit has the ability to mix all that’s good with all that’s hood and give the crowd a show to remember!

Growing up in Jersey City, N.J. as an eighty’s baby, Conceit was exposed to the true roots of hip hop at an early age. Influenced by Mc’s such as Rakim, Nas, Big Daddy Kane, and Jay-Z as well as groups like Pubic Enemy and A Tribe Called Quest, he learned to respect the art of putting words together not just to rhyme, but to express oneself. Living in places such as: Atlanta, Texas, and California have also had a strong impact on Conceits music. He blends his lyrical abilities with the bounce and party feel of down south and west coast hip hop, a pleasure to behold!

Conceit has shared the stage with Major artist such as The Ying Yang Twins, E-40, Too Short, Twista, Bone Thugs in Harmony, Dj Unk, Paul Wall, Chamillionaire and Mistah F.A.B. After every show the fans are talking about much more than just the Major artist! 07/05/11 marked the release of Conceit third album titled “PERFECTION”. This CD will be Conceit’s first with major backing and distribution and is expected to turn a lot of heads. His first two albums “Classic” (may08) and “I Shall Be Heard” (apr09) were both released with limited availability but will one day be seen as diamonds in the ruff…

It was once said that hip hop is dead, well Conceit looks pretty good for a dead guy because he is hip hop. If u enjoy good music in general (not just rap) you should keep an ear out for this kid. He is destined for great things!

title: When G's Pray
extra:
When G's Pray is actually a true story. If you pay attention to the lyrics, you will catch a glimpse of what it was like for me growing up in the Caribbean hood, and the street fight with my stepdad i had to survive on my own... FYI.... he had a gun and i still won the fight...LISTEN TO THE SONG ......DO YOU GET IT NOW? True story.... really against the odds. Enjoy and don't forget to leave some feedback.
This is a work in progress so.... expect more..... and better!!!!

HERE'S THE COMPLETE LYRICS TO THE SONG:

INTRO:
(THE DISTORTED VOICE YOU HEAR IN THE BEGINNING OF THE SONG IS THE FIRST TWO VERSES OF THE LORD'S PRAYER PLAYED IN REVERSE)\u003E\u003E\u003E\u003E
(THIS IS DONE MERELY TO REACH ALL INTUITIVE MINDS THAT PAY ATTENTION TO SYMBOLISM AND ENCOURAGE RELIGIOUS FANATICS TO LISTEN WITH AN OPEN MIND... I AM ONLY HUMAN.... THEREFOR, I DIGRESS.)

CHORUS:
As I... lay my... head down... to sleep
I pray... the Lord.... my soul... to keep
And if I.. should die... before I... awake
I pray... the lord... my soul.... to take

Verse 1:
I wrote a suicide note on the same blunt i rolled the weed with
No time for heartbreaks; let it burn... on some G shit
Real recognizes the real... so what's the deal
With these down-pressing niggaz suppressing my good deeds
They even breath condescendingly, echoing growls
'Round every ghetto showdown... you'll see a cheering crowd
Stand in awe while I crack his jaw... Him alone was armed
But the left hook was flawless and quicker to draw
And I swore... they all should've stopped me in the womb
Fuck em' all... my attitude properly introduced you to war
Mama still prays for the kids
My middle finger flips and parts the Red Sea when i'm pissed
(repeat next four bars twice)
Wise men and common fools live on parallel lines
We 're both divided by wisdom, but we all know to die
So why can't you nor I..... turn the other cheek
I'd die on my feet.... before I live live on my knees
When Gs pray....

(repeat Chorus)

title: One More
extra:
Signal 99 has emerged from New Mexico as the hot new influential metal sound in the southwest with the release of their new CD, “The Gospel”. Winners of the Ernie Ball Battle of the Bands in the New Mexico Region, they opened up the Rockstar Energy Drink Uproar Festival. Also nominated for two categories for the 2011 Native American Music Awards. Signal 99 was recently featured as part of FUSE MUSIC TV’s “Slave To The Metal” tour they took the night with solid fan support. They returned to the road in March 2011 for a featured SXSW MusicGorilla Showcase and the Heart of Texas Rockfest appearances in support of their new CD “The Gospel” and the must see controversial new video for the anti-hate rock anthem, ”Banner Of Corpses” on You Tube. The groundbreaking video delivers a message of racial tolerance while revealing a shocking link between the Jewish holocaust and the Native American genocide. Signal 99 has built a considerable radio and TV presence that continues to grow a large online footprint. Recently nominated for the 2011 Native American Awards for "Best Debut Artist" and "Best Music Video."

The Signal 99 intense sound is fronted by singer/songwriter/lead guitarist Chuck Haven and backed by a pounding rhythm duo of the striking sonic and visual presence of “Krave” on bass along with the power drumming of Mark Curley. Signal 99 can back it up on the road and have been hard at work touring in seven states, headlining and sharing the stage with top rock/metal acts, including Avenged Sevenfold, Seether, Three Days Grace, Sevendust, Powerman 5000, Kittie, Ill Nino, Nonpoint, Green Jelly, Ekotren, DIECAST, Dine Alone, I.R.A.T.E., Nuumak, and Psychostick.

Their new release delivers a message that will continue to show what Metal Horizon Magazine has already praised the group for with it’s “strong vocals and intense sound” and that the Signal 99 style of playing, “has an opportunity to influence a different sound of metal to the metal scene."

The Signal 99 media profile continues to rise nationally, with over 126,000+ views, 40,500+ fans, and 81,000+ plays on MySpace.

title: I'LL REMEMBER YOU
extra:
Jon Lindquist
Accoustic Rhythm - Vocals

Jon Lindquist is a hall-of-fame radio announcer whose voice has been heard by millions; and he has been a vital part of the Las Vegas radio landscape for over 20 years. Jon originally hales from Montana and loves playing music.

Annette Hasalone
Lead Guitar - Vocals

Dr. Annette Hasalone is a well-known Naturopathic Doctor who has been listed in the Marqui's Who's Who since 2003. Having developed a full line of products for her company Elemental Research Inc., Dr. Annette is both an innovator and inventor. In addition, she has been a prominent radio-broadcaster for almost 15 years. She is originally from Northern California and has been playing guitar and singing since she was very young.

Garret Capler
Drums - Vocals

Though the band calls him "Gary," Garret has been active in music most of his life; in a variety of styles; in a variety of roles; and on a variety of instruments. Jon and Annette refer to Gary as the "icing on their musical cake." His talent, keen sense of humor, boyish charm, and love of music are elements The Honorifics wouldn't be the same without.

Thaddeus Corea
Bass - Drums - Vocals

If the name Corea sounds familiar, it should: Thaddeus is the son of jazz-legend Chick Corea. While he often refers to himself as a drummer, his bass playing has been the foundation for artists as diverse as Blue Man Group and Wild Colonials. He is also owner of the coolest recording studio in Las Vegas: Jaguar Recording Studio. Thaddeus' musical interests and tastes run the gamut; hence his interest in The Honorifics.

If the name Corea sounds familiar, it should: Thaddeus is the son of jazz-legend Chick Corea. While he often refers to himself as a drummer, his bass playing has been the foundation for artists as diverse as Blue Man Group and Wild Colonials. He is also owner of the coolest recording studio in Las Vegas: Jaguar Recording Studio. Thaddeus' musical interests and tastes run the gamut; hence his interest in The Honorifics.

title: Ooh Boy (Radio Edit)
extra:
Alicia Saldenha's unique sound can be described as funky soul with a twist of island sugar cane. A national of the Caribbean island Republic of Trinidad and Tobago, she resides in Japan where she is a rising star in the independent soul music scene. In 2011 she collaborated with the successful instrumental nu jazz group, indigo jam unit, on the album Rose and a tour of Japan. She has also performed with the legendary Paul Jackson of Herbie Hancock and the Headhunters.


“Ooh Boy” is an up-tempo, feel-good, romantic reggae song, guaranteed to bring a smile to your face. It has proved immensely popular in Japan with both Japanese and foreign audiences at performances by soul singer-songwriter, Alicia Saldenha. It was produced by Andrew Felluss (Radian Records) & co-poduced by Alicia Saldenha.

title: I Made it! A Cancer Survivor Song

extra:
FEATHERFOOT MUSIC
Bill & Brenda recognized that in today’s electronic online music world where the CD is virtually dead that they needed to move their music into the new age, so they came up with “Featherfoot Music”, which is not a Band in the technical sense. They write lyrics and compose music and then produce & mix the music for a majority of their songs in their studio in Central, FL. They also team up and take advantage of local talent but also other music professionals and vocalists from almost anywhere on the planet. They found in this new online age it was possible to globally find and work with many talented people. Their first CD “Featherfoot Music” was published in 2009 via CD baby and is also available on iTunes. They have more than fifty songs placed with a music publisher in LA for TV and movies, including music aired on The Discovery Channel show “Auction Kings” in 2013 season 4. And we also had a song aired on the PBS Nova show "Making Stuff Wilder". Recently we placed two songs for an independent movie being filmed in Uruguay. We have also have had a few holds from some publishers and Record Company’s.

Fou Nature are a six piece act, one of their reasons for forming was to create “positive messages for youth at risk and underprivileged children.

Fou Nature have captured the Love! Pop songs for everyone that rejuvenate your love for life and the happiness it brings. Entertainers whose very essence and vitality have you feeling that your worries are far far away. Warm and inviting Fou Nature's upbeat and positive lyrics reach across and embrace Auckland's diverse culture - spreading good vibes and a zest for life. "We believe happy people make a difference" says Asey Lio, member of Fou Nature after the release of their latest single 'Ooh Ooh Song' "Having our songs played on National Radio & TV in New Zealand (South Pacific) has been a huge buzz" Asey says; also commenting that 'Ooh Ooh Song' has been voted the Number 1 single on an American music site. "We love writing songs but most of all we love playing live and watching the spirits of the audience lift. It really is something quite magical to watch" Experienced professional musicians, Fou Nature are the ideal band for your entertainment. They are able to play as a 3-piece or up to a 7-piece band, or depending on your requirements.

title: Scientists
extra:
The Sons is a five-piece indie rock band hailing from Derby, England, comprised of Paul Herron, Lee Blades, Stewart English, Roger Millichamp and Steven Herron.

Drawing from a wide variety of influences - from Brit Pop to Alternative Rock, R&B, and Folk – their songs blend thought-provoking lyrics with equally complex, highly melodic instrumentation.

Known for their clever songwriting, high-energy live shows and witty, charismatic, sometimes zany antics, the band members delight fans by poking fun at themselves as well as their audience.

Since 2007, The Sons have released two full-length albums and toured Europe extensively. They are signed to Popup Records in Continental Europe and Cannon Fodder Recordings in all other global territories. The band is represented by Magnolia Artist Management in the US.

title: Born Again (What About The Child)
extra: I am a survivor of child abuse...of much abuse. just listen. Here's to the Peter Pan's and TinkerBelle's. Jesus Loves you. God loves you. It's okay to be in NeverNeverLand and to go back and it's okay not to grow up and it's okay to always be a child and to be a woman and a man and a boy and a girl and to never ever hurt again. it's okay to be a warrior and and child and to love and to hate and to want revenge and want someone to get that revenge for you. You are not alone. I hope you know that. I need to always know that to. THis is NeoWorship for us, for you and me. For the angels that did not fall by choice but that...well.

album: The Diary Of A Hopeless Romantic
title: Untitled
Engaged Souls
extra:
First album of Demian Grace - «Right Signs» was recorded by Roman Olkhovka on his laptop with two guitars and one mic in 2008 in Moscow. But this work attracted attention of Jon Letts - british musician and producer from Leicester, UK.
He decided to make new mix of this record in his home studio, but after that he still wanted something more and he offered to record something new together. That was start of recording sessions for second album of Demian Grace - «Little Song For Darling».
Some new musicians also co-worked with them: Ruslan Olkhovka from Krasnoyarsk (bass) and Alexey Krivobok from St. Petersburg(guitar). They sent recorded parts to Jon over Internet. Roman recorded vocals and acoustic guitar parts in specially rented studio in Moscow. Jon recorded drums and mixed all together. That way «Little Song For Darling» was finished in the beginning of 2009.
Next summer Roman shooted first music videos for Demian Grace: «Right Signs» and «Ain’t Wrong», simultaneously working on the new recordings. In «Ain’t Wrong» video he was shooted with talented russian rising movie star Evgenia Osipova.
New album titled «Ain’t Wrong» was finished in 2010, and then Roman moved to his native Siberia for gathering full live band there.
After that they started work on the next album, which will be available much soon. It’s called «Saving Love» and consists no sampled or synthesized sounds through it. Everything is much live now.

Demian Grace now are:

Roman Olkhovka - vocals, guitars
Alexander Elizar’ev - drums
Ruslan Olkhovka - bass
Pavel Kuznetsov - guitar
Anna Miheeva - violin

title: Never Let It Go
extra:
THE SPINS are an Italian pop/rock outfit headed by Alessia Mattalia, arguably Europes best known female drummer having done session work for Jeff Beck and particularly noted for her drumming on Jeff Beck's Grammy Award winning track ‘HAMMERHEAD’ featured on the album ‘Emotion and Commotion’. Their EP ‘Hello Baby’ reached #14 in RadioWaveMonitor Electronic/Dance charts and the video won a special prize at the Chicago Planet Ant Film and Video Festival.

Alessia formed The Spins with keyboard player and composer Marcello Giordano, best known for his European dance hit ‘I wish You’. The Spins line up is completed by French female bassist Silvia Cernicchiaro, guitarist Mario Pignatelli with lead vocals provided by Michelangelo Alesso

The recording and production of the single ‘Never Let it Go’ was split between the UK and the US, with drums and vocals recorded here at Prism Studio and produced by Stuart Epps (Elton John, Led Zeppelin, Oasis and Chris Rea). Stuart even provided backing vocals. Grammy Award winning Producer Jeff Bova (Celine Dion, Michael Jackson, Eric Clapton, and Billy Joel) completed the recording and production in his studio in LA, adding his own keyboards to the track.

Having previously successfully toured the UK twice, the band are set to tour these shores again later this year.

title: INTO THE BLUE
extra:
The Into The Blue EP is the first release containing tracks taken from Chris Ford’s new album The Light On The Hill which is due for release in 2011. This follows on from the fantastic reaction Chris received for his 2008 album, All Caught Up and the critically acclaimed success of his 2006 début This Atlantic Low.
The EP includes the songs, Into The Blue, The Warp Glass plus two tracks recorded live at BBC radio sessions ; Everything and The Final Word.
While the approach is similar to the stripped down essence of All Caught Up, the sound of the tracks and the forthcoming album incorporates a wider musical landscape in terms of the arrangements and instrumentation.
Chris's music is something that is in short supply across the current musical landscape, he is a real storyteller. He has something to say and he uses strong melodic hooks and structure to create songs which could all be movie scripts. His voice has a soulful purity and depth that resonates with the listener long after the songs have ended.

extra: Hey there... I'm Glenn and I'm a songwriter from New Jersey. Some people say my songs stink, to which I say, "Oh yeah??? What do you know about music, Paul McCartney??" Sheesh. A guy writes some of the most beloved songs of our time and suddenly he thinks he's an EXPERT or something! Well, I say let's show "the cute one" what real music is by supporting my songs! YAY! Or... not. Well, either way, thanks for your time. Sincerely, Glenn

extra: A song about a life changing trip I took in January of this year.

title: Sw33tness
extra: Tenor Sax feature - an adventure in plastic jazz inspired by a chill groove I wrote a few years ago.

title: It Stunk Up the Room
extra: Altos shouldn't have all the fun. Tenor sax can be funky too. This is a princey, pfunky jazz thing I came with this last week...it's super fun times (for me it was anyway)

title: Two Hearts Are There
extra:
I am very interested in improving my songwriting ability. It would be great to have one of my songs recorded by a known or up and coming artist. I am also interested in collaboration and feedback is always welcome. I have little interest in performing or pursuing a career in the music business other than songwriting. Just trying to make a decent sounding demo, not trying to cut album quality.
I played all the instruments and drums were achieved with a drum machine.

title: All You Ever Say is Goodbye
My Dearest Hip Hop
extra: One of the Best Hip Hop Songs Ever.... Song is A love letter to Hip-Hop that talks about some of her fallen soldiers such as Biggie, Big Pun, And Pimp C.

title: Fanta Pants
extra:
Recorded and mixed at Hothouse Audio St Kilda by Jez Giddings
Produced by Craig Harnath and Destroy She Said
Mastered by Jack the Bear at Deluxe Mastering.
Destroy She Said are:
Youngy - guitar | Dave Walker - guitar | Scampers - bass | Simon McCullough - vocals | Greg Aldridge - drums.

title: Game Over
extra:
Hailing from Melbourne, Australia, Destroy She Said's music is a potent blend of vicious guitar riffs mixed with tales of fast living. It’s the soundtrack to Melbourne’s underbelly; stripped back, hard edged, no bullshit rock n roll.
Their second EP, Music For Muscle Cars, was recorded at Hothouse Audio in St Kilda and mastered by Jack the Bear at Deluxe. It contains four of the toughest and most honest rock songs you are likely to hear all year.
All DSS music is available on iTunes and Bandcamp.

title: Ribbon Of Life
extra:
Riding on this ribbon of life I've been given
Learning my lessons day by day.
My life is wrapped around this spirit within me
that will bring me home when I let it lead the way.

Tossing and turning with the storms my soul encounters
sometimes leaves me hanging by a thread.
I'd surely lose my grip by now if I hadn't learned
that storms clear leaving sunny skies ahead ~
Keep on looking for those sunny skies ahead.

So please be patient with this restlessness I'm feeling
My spirit yearns to be set free
from this world's fears and man-made chains and limitations
that have no place inside of me ~
There's no place for them inside of me.

Riding on this ribbon of life I've been given
Learning my lessons day by day.
My life is wrapped around this spirit within me
that will bring me home when I let it lead the way ~
When I let it lead the way!

title: Been That Mean
extra:
She was one of the prettiest teachers I'd seen
but she had one eye that looked at him
and one eye that looked at me
And we'd both pretend we didn't know which one
that she was trying to see.

Oh yeah, kids can be cruel, and I was no exception.
I made fun of that teacher and spent time in detention,
And it finally got so bad that she didn't want me
in her class anymore . . .
She even moved my desk outside the door.

She was a teacher who LOVED her work ~ till I came along
for I made her feel just like she didn't belong
And it was only because her eyes were different from ours ~
spread apart from the time she was born.
But she had such a caring heart that was friendly and warm.

One day news came around ~ that teacher finally had left.
And the days passed without her ~ Still no sign of her yet.
And I felt really bad that maybe I'd made her quit
for I knew that I'd hurt that teacher . . . quite a bit. . .

Well, the new year of school began ~ and who did I see?!
It was that same pretty teacher ~ and she looked straight at me!
Her eyes were no longer set apart like before,
And she was looking quite happy, and feeling quite self assured!

And I hope she still teaches ~ for she sure did teach me
about getting past obstacles to be who you want to be.
And though I never told her ~ well, just between you and me ~
she was one of the prettiest teachers that I'd ever seen,
and how I wish that I had never been that mean.
Oh no, I wish that I had NEVER
been that mean.

title: Blown
extra: If there was a magic elixir for connecting the right artists, it would be a highly coveted formula. With combined influences ranging from Foo Fighters and Queens of the Stone Age, to Aerosmith and Led Zeppelin, the members of Beyond the Cage are grateful that their respective muses turned out to be so compatible. The result is hard-driving tunes with rich melodic overtones. A shared sense of what’s truly important in life. A desire to bring into being what should be… Life beyond the cage!

Rick Gardner’s musical journey has been a very strange ride. Bustin Bob Mitchell, the noted Cincinnati, OH Funk Journalist, said “Gardner’s resulting “rubberhorn” sound is now emerging. This is an unfeigned and unique mix of latin-influenced rhythms, ambient textures, raw funk grooves, techno and neo-jazz interposing. All flawlessly interpreted by this master player with over 40 exhilarating years of veteran experience in his chops”. P-Funk radio’s JTRP aka Keith Jackson recently said “Your music is like a movie sound track….sounds like something’s about to happen!”
Rick has spent the last few years developing a music production studio for the purpose of licensing his music through various online sources.
For over 40 years he toured the world with Bill Chase, Marvin Gaye, Bootsy Collins, and George Clinton. Fred Wesley, Maceo Parker, Kush Griffith and Rick were the world famous “Horny Horns”. He played electric trumpet with Ray “Doors” Manzarek at the Whiskey A Go Go with guest artist Iggy Pop. In July of 2002 he performed at the ESPY Awards show with Snoop Dogg and Bootsy Collins hosted by Samuel L Jackson. He is on the Brian Culbertson CD “Bringing Back the Funk”. One of his co-written works, Lickety Split aired on Saturday Night Live. He has received several RIAA awards.
"Who would have thought that somebody coming out of Wichita would have done things with these kind of people.” THE WICHITA EAGLE by Kevin Sheedy Sunday, September 17, 2000 Section: ARTS & LEISURE Edition: main page: 1D You can find more information about Rick or listen to his music at http://www.rubberhorn.com

title: Hey Hey (Every Time I get this Feeling)
extra:
My Name is Theo Starr, which is what I use as a composer, my stage name is Theo Starr aka The Technician when I play live.

Consider myself more of a Musician/Songwriter – Producer/Songwriter than a Singer/Songwriter.

But Predominately, a Writer first, a Musician second, a Producer third and an Artist fourth. But that all changes for convenience and when it is convenient depending on circumstances.

At the moment self-publishing and self-producing and trying to expand from that platform by obtaining licensing deals for soundtracks and/or have other artists perform and record my material. Distributions of my Material can be found on iTunes, Google Play and Amazon.

I do play live, and have had lead my own band, but at present playing my material acoustically while filling in for other bands.

My material is totally and utterly 100% mine, produced and composed and I have a catalogue of almost 200 compositions of which only a percentage would be for public consumption which, at the moment is totaling 40 and heading up as I write more, while I challenge myself to be consistent using that one breaking composition as a spring board.

I have my own Studio Set Up. Pro Tools is my software of choice and I can supply tracks as audio, with or without vocals with any desired mix.
I play Guitar and Bass on my tracks, I do program a Drum Machine (Superior Drummer) which is a plug in within Pro Tools and when I need a synth or a keyboard, I have a guitar synth or I can program the sound within the Pro Tools plug ins or with other tools at my disposal.

I consider my genre to be, Progressive Rock – Adult Contemporary Alternative but will challenge myself to write in other genres to obtain recognition. Especially that sub-genre referred to as Blaxploitation.

For further references, please go to ReverbNation and my WebSite

http://www.reverbnation.com/TheoStarrTheTech
http://thetechakatheostarr.com/

There is music, videos, photos, blogs, comments and links to my distributions and SoundCloud.

I am based in Sydney, Australia and I can be contacted on the following details:

Phone (Mobile): +61 0416-278747
email: almity1@ozemail.com.au
Skype: Theo Starr

extra:
A Super blend of rock and soul, characterize the sound from this Boston based band Ya. Born and raised in Massachusetts, former teacher, and singer songwriter, George Thomas fills his songs with passion and vivid detail. Thomas’s music is personal, political, and universally appealing. Thomas's thought-provoking lyrics, and dynamic mix of acoustic and electric guitars, symphonic percussion and background singers carries a feeling to all his listeners. His work has been stated as a mix of the Moody Blues and Roy Orbison. Ya and George Thomas are totally original.
fine blend of sweet country soul
My story is simple but true,
I stepped out of my house one night and crossed into the backyard,when suddenly a flash of red light and a shattering sound engulfed me, how long I tumbled through space and time and endured that noise I don’t remember, all I know is that when it stopped I found myself in this vast tall grass field. The wind was howling around me and twin moons blazed brightly in that cambium sky.
Up ahead on a grassy knoll I could see a castle in the distance. Upon arriving at it's drawbridge I called out but only an echo came back to haunt me I searched every room in this place, but I am all alone! One of the rooms had a guitar leaning up against a chair with a note lying beside it, "play me and you will be heard it read". I thought of Alice in Wonderland and the “drink me” bottles on the table. So now I hope someone will hear my song. George Thomas!
Georgethomas.tv

Bruce Bergh’s newest 2012 release, “Chicago Night Life” is a collection of original “Rat-Pack” tunes written during 2011 as a nightlife entertainer in some of Chicago’s finest dining establishments. Bergh performs on piano with vocal stylings in the Pop, Rock and Jazz Vocal genres. As a composer, he strives for memorable melody lines accompanied by jazz harmonizations with a positive message.

Bergh studied at Sherwood Music School and the University of Chicago, and has written hundreds of songs, commercial music and jingles, as well as arranged music for a large number of clients through the years at his three recording studios. As a professor of Music Technology, Bergh taught in four universities, done clinician work for MTNA, MENC, and NAMM conventions, and founded The Bergh Institute of Music Technology (BIMT.net and DrMIDI.com).

Some of Bergh’s career highlights include playing organ for the Chicago Cubs at Wrigley Field, performing live with Kerry Livgren of “Kansas” on synthesizer, pianist/vocalist for Willow Creek Community Chapel events, traveling North America as a product specialist and clinician for numerous musical instrument manufacturers, collaborating with Bob Moog & Ray Kurzweil regarding synthesizer technology and sales, and leading worship and performing in many top churches, theaters and convention centers across the United States.


Bruce Bergh’s Discography:

“Chicago Night Life” a CD collection of new “Rat-Pack” styled originals. 2012

“Taxi Portfolio 2011” is an eclectic collection of tunes written for Taxi A&R in 2011

“Christmas Time of the Year” a CD collection of Christmas originals released in November 2011

“Christmas Time of the Year” a single released on iTunes 2010

“Family Album” a CD collection of music written about his family released in 2010 as an Independent Artist

“Paradise” a CD collection of original Contemporary Christian (CCM) songs released in 2009 by BIMT Studios.

“Body Language: An Excercise in Excessive Sampling Abuse” a 45 single released in 1988 by Rednose Records (Flip side of "Dubois Boys")

"Dubois Boys" a Novelty Polka 45 RPM single released in 1988 by Rednose Records

title: Diva
extra:
It is often said, when opportunity meets preparation success soon follows. Well, Ariana Stewart, the self proclaimed “Street Diva” has been preparing since the age of 12 years old. She has been honing her skills as a singer, songwriter, vocal arranger, and entertainer. During this time Ariana has learned from average everyday producers and artists all the way up to the legendary in the game and has amassed a body of musical works that has garnered industry attention around the world.
Numerous opportunities have been knocking and Ariana -2MCH4YA MUSIC PUBLISHING, has made the decision to ink a non-exclusive co-publishing deal with Andrew Lane’s “Drew Right Music.” (http://www.myspace.com/drewright) With the ink barely dry on the contract, Ariana was tapped to write a song for a major project and will be collaborating with Drewright Music/ on numerous other major projects in the near future.
Born in Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania by way of Ozark, Alabama, to two very proud parents; mother - Shannon, and father - Willie Lee Stewart, Ariana’s early musical talents were evident when her mother would sing gospel and country songs to her, and Ariana would sing them back. Now at the age of 19, with song writing in every genre at the core of her creativity, Ariana is poised to finally make her mark on the industry. Successful and established industry veteran Andrew Lane, believes in Ariana and her abilities to write hits so stay tuned. The best is yet to come.

title: Candy Heart
extra:
Formed in 2007, Romeo Spike is a 4 piece modern rock group based in Atlanta, GA.  Their line-up features: Michael Kunz (Chicago, IL - lead vocals, Rhodes electric piano & guitar) - Donn Aaron (Pensacola FL - lead guitar, pedal steel & backing vocals) - Skyler Ross (Atlanta, GA - bass & backing vocals) and Owen Liversidge (Glastonbury, England - drums, programming & backing vocals.) The group began performing in 2009 and their debut full length album "For The Cause" was self-recorded and co-produced by Matt Still (Elton John.) In the band's first efforts to promote "For The Cause", multiple national album and show reviews have described Romeo Spike as innovative with a futuristic flair who take the best elements of yesterday and push them toward the limits of tomorrow.

Music video "Star Power": 
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4Xx_wjraRVw 

About the group name:
A literary allusion, the artistic and almost mockingly decorative Romeo Spikes were meant to keep young "Romeos" from climbing up the poles to meet their "Juliets" in the balconies of 19th Century Spanish townhouses of New Orleans. The presence of a diminished number of Romeo Spikes remain still today in the French Quarter and also sprinkled throughout Savannah, GA, Charleston, SC and Pensacola, FL.

website: www.romeospike.com

Pieces of You
extra:
"The new Mad Planet EP is reflection of love and commitment. The tracks take a voyage into the ebbs and flows of human emotion – the highs, lows and every inkling in between. Though written through the eyes of Gillepsie’s personal experiences with bandmate Greg Gordon (The Nervous Return), the EP humanizes our most irrational feelings of elation and doubt and the ability to overcome our greatest fears which can lead to our greatest accomplishments. Mad Planet leads the listener into an intimate and relatable journey through the path Gillespe and Gordon have taken throughout their path as bandmates, as a couple and as soon-to-be husband and wife. Produced by Ethan Allen (The 88, Tricky, Gram Rabbit), the latest release departs slightly from the band’s trip-hop roots exposing layers of pulsating bass lines, sexy guitars and punchy drums which allow Cooper Gillespie’s (Bang Sugar Bang, co-creater of the Kiss or Kill movement) sultry vocals to float effortlessly above.

The lead track from the Mad Planet EP, Pieces of You, has won “Best Electronic Song” in the Malibu Music Awards and has also been nominated for “Best Alternative Song” by the Hollywood Music and Media Awards.

In 2010, the band’s debut album, All Elephants (2010), was a soulful exploration of loss and heartbreak that garnered the band critical acclaim and position in the CMJ Top 200 charts alongside bands such as Arcade Fire, Interpol and Of Montreal. Hot on the debut release’s heels, Mad Planet released the Gliese 581g EP which propelled them into touring throughout North America sharing the stage with the likes of Foster the People, Gram Rabbit and He’s My Brother She’s My Sister."

-http://popyoularity.com

extra:
Luanne Hunt is an award-winning, Grammy-balloted recording artist from Southern California, who records on the Independent label, Star Creek Records.

Throughout her illustrious career as an Indie artist, Hunt has built an impressive list of accomplishments and a worldwide fan base with her refreshing and well-crafted country folk tunes. Her 2007 CD, “Breaking Through, ” has produced two hit singles on U.S. and European Charts. The enchanting “Solace In The Wind” reached No. 1 the European Country Music Association’s chart (Belgium) in July, 2010.

The tune, which was written by Hunt’s husband Steve, peaked at No. 37 on the Indie World Country Chart, which is the largest and oldest independent music chart in the genre.

Recording industry executive Dale Kawashima, formerly of Giant and Mercury Records, named “Solace in the Wind” one of the Top Five Songs of the Month for September, 2008 on his popular website, Songwriter Universe. Additionally, the song landed on the 2009 Grammy ballot in two categories: Best Female Country Performance and Best Country Song.

In 2009, Hunt’s infectious song “The Sun’s Coming Up Over Memphis” reached No. 10 on the New Music Weekly country chart, garnering an incredible 37,000 radio spins worldwide.

"Luanne's voice is beautiful and haunting and reminiscent of a female version of Simon and Garfunkel,” said Bobby Jo Valentine of Music Worth Reviewing. “Her lyrics are powerful, her musicianship is solid, and there's simply a thousand things to love about this artist. She will be sure to go far."

Luanne Hunt began pursuing a professional music career in the mid-1990s. She found immediate success with her critically-acclaimed single “I Don’t Bother Counting,” which was frequently played on the former KIK FM country radio station in Orange County, California and on other stations throughout the Southwest. In 1996, Luanne shared the bill with Billy Ray Cyrus, Tammy Wynette, Toby Keith and Martina McBride at Starfest Country Music Festival at the Los Angeles County Fairgrounds.

Over the years, many of Hunt’s songs have been played on AM, FM, Satellite and Internet stations around the world. In 2007, Luanne was featured on an “On-Air” interview on the “Steve and Johnnie Show” on Chicago’s WGN Radio. She was named “Christmas Star of the Day” in December, 2008 on Doug Stephan’s popular “Good Day” syndicated radio program.

Along with “Breaking Through,” Luanne has two other CDs, “The Singles Sessions” and “How Christmas Feels To Me.”

title: The Things I Found In You
A Generic Cute Song For A One of A Kind Girl
We're Not in Kansas Anymore
extra:
Breaking out of the norm in The Jersey Shore, the members of A Tale to Tell prove that if you have passion, you can achieve anything. Beginning March 2011, Blake D’Uva, Nick Semanchik, Ryan Gobel, John Reagan, and Matt Flanagan started achieving what takes most bands years to accomplish. With their hard work and determination, you can be certain that they will not be stopped.

Their debut single “Room for Two” was released June 2011 on iTUNES, with their EP “A New Direction” following shortly after in November. A Tale to Tell combines genuine musical talent with rhythms that take you in and spit you out. “Stay Close to Home” showcases that they can also steal your girlfriends’ heart with acoustic settings, while “Get Over It” will make it hard for you to stand still and look depressed. Their complete seven track EP “A New Direction” will quickly make its’ way onto your favorite playlists in no time.


2012 holds new things in store for A Tale to Tell. With an all-new single “Radio,” featuring Will Cruz, to a music video releasing in April, the party is just getting started and fans can be assured that these guys will be around for a long time.


Keep connected and updated by liking A Tale to Tells’ facebook page and following their twitter, you don’t want to miss out on what’s coming next

title: To Lay Beside You A While
extra: Hello! My name is David Woods, a songwriter! "To Lay Beside You A While" took me years to write because of the emotional aspect of the song. As you read the lyrics you will see that it is about a man who found out he is dying and can't wait to be with his deceased wife whom he misses terribly so he goes to her grave to talk to her one last time and "To Lay Beside You A While." It was originally written in two parts, a main body and a reprise, but, I decided to put them together to tell the whole story at once. I hope you enjoy "To Lay Beside You A While" and thanks for listening! Have a great day!! David Woods

title: "Reflections"
extra:
"Iniquitous..." That best describes the foundation of "13", says singer songwriter Neal Sowers. "This band is very unique in it's own way. I wanted it to be as pure & real as it gets in this band. Not packed full of shit that cannot be duplicated live on stage, honest and to the point", as he reaches for his slide. “We’re focused on getting real solid rock back into the scene without all the fluff. The incorporation of the slide with heavy rock is something you don't hear much of anymore, but I fucking love it!- It gives the music a sense of a, dark edged southern vibe, meets hot rods and pin ups. Can't go wrong there!" After the 2008 release of "Virgo Rising", Neal moved from Arizona to Los Angeles with one goal in mind....music. After a year of false starts and shake-ups he finally found a group of like minded guys that were just as enthusiastic to rock, and, they were willing to back the songs. After teaming up with Bryan Sinklier (drums), Roy Sherman (rhythm guitar) and AJ Shafi (bass guitar), they were all ready to get their feet off the ground and play", says Neal. The band has played a wide array of venues from all over the Sunset Strip in Los Angeles, to MMA fights getting the crowd pumped for beatdown action.

Neal’s been picked up and endorsed by Line 6 amplification & GHS guitar strings. The band is known for a killer rock show and sound. Follow them online at; www.13rock.com and stay in the loop. Been told it's, "highly enjoyable with whiskey", undoubtedly so, but really enjoyed when played loud. Catch a live show. ---Cheers---

title: Goin Goin Gone
extra:
“People are tired of being depressed. Times are hard right now and we all know that, so at the end of the week when you’ve busted your ass, do you really want to sit around and be put to sleep? No, you want to break open a case with some friends and have a good time. “-Ump (Lead VOX/Guitar)
Westville, OK based Motortrain takes that statement to heart, bringing what can only be described as a true rock and roll party to every live show they play, and somehow capturing that feeling on their debut EP “Straight Six” as well. It’s a no-holds-barred brand of southern-flavored down and dirty rock with six straight-to-the-point tracks that fans really relate to. Recorded and produced by Mike Bolenbach at Full Well Studios in Phoenix, AZ and co-produced by Louis Lashes, the members of Motortrain stood strong against the use of bells, whistles, and modern over-production to dress up their album. The band's frontman, Ump says, “We're going back to basics. We wanted a classic sounding, sonic punch to the throat. No autotune or layers of guitars. Just vocals, two guitars, bass and drums. Nothing more, nothing less.”

All in all, it's rough, it's unpolished, it's remarkably bare...but the journey has to begin somewhere.

title: (you)niverse demo
extra:
How long has it been since you witnessed the stars in flight?
They've waited for you 'til they faded in the morning light.
They've waited for your eyes to glow with light from outer space,
And they've longed to illuminate the wonder on your face.
Step outside and let the starlight bathe you in its grace,
Let the cosmic river flowing take you to some secret place.
There is so much more to see than you've allowed yourself to see,
Because you've locked yourself into a life of who they want you to be,
And you never see the stars anymore.
You just hurry on inside and lock the door.

You are the universe,
And the universe is you.
Rid your inner circle
Of the line that passes through.
Open up your eyes,
And let your mind follow through.
Beauty is a state of mind,
And it all begins with you.

I'm no prophet,
I'm no priest.
I'm just another soul-brother who's a lover of discovery
At the very least.
I don't have it all figured out,
No, I don't expect to have it soon.
But in the meantime I'll be just fine
Building ladders to the moon
The astral ocean's begging you to come and take a swim.
Hey, the universe feels fine, come on and jump right in.

You are the universe,
And the universe is you.
Rid your inner circle
Of the line that passes through.
Open up your eyes,
And your mind will follow through.
Beauty is a state of mind,
And it all begins with you.

The constellations as our destination,
We aspire to the aura.
Leaping over gravity, astrological nirvana.
If it takes a million years for man to learn to love, then let it be,
Hey, that's fine with me, because I'll be living astronomically.

Because I am the universe,
And the universe is me.
I have rid my inner circle
Of the line that inhibits me.
Open up your eyes,
Let your mind follow through, you'll see.
Beauty is a state of mind,
And it starts with being free.

title: Little Bird
extra:
Left your place at daybreak,
And I slept straight through the sun.
Woke up in the dark,
And cleared away the web I'd spun.
Remembering your whisper
Set me free from all alarms,
And all at once I wished
I could be back in your arms.

Little bird, please don't fly away.
I am here, I am strong, and I am here to stay.
Let me hold you in my hand and keep you warm,
For the bird is solemn that flies through the storm.
So little bird, please don't fly away.

You are the sky,
In more ways than I can name.
And I am the ocean
In more ways than I care to claim.
The sea doesn't touch the sky,
No, the clouds don't touch the brine.
But all we need is the sun
To make this painting turn out fine.

Little bird, please don't leave me be,
For the comfort that I've found within your eyes is such a rarity.
And if you still want to fly when our time is done,
I'll set you free and watch you fly into the sun,
But little bird, please don't leave me be.

I've never flown,
Never tried to spread my wings,
But I have always wondered
Just what makes the song bird sing.
You and I could fly,
Tear our names through the sky.
Leave uncertainty on the land,
And to our troubles say goodbye.

Little bird, please come fly with me.
Don't have a penny to my name, but I've got dreamer's wings.
And if we just come crashing down to the sand,
I know we'll find a softer place than here to land,
So little bird, please come fly with me.

Little bird, please come fly with me.

title: sea, sky, tree. (new demo)
extra:
Excuse me, Mr. Sycamore tree,
Could you please teach me how to breathe?
I shed my leaves for the winter,
Now I can't find my center,
And I and need to rebuild me.
Oh, please, Mr. Sycamore tree,
Teach me how to find my roots,
To know where I've been.
I'll tap into the ground on this earth that I've found,
And I hope that it will let me in.

But, pardon me, you beautiful tree,
Who am I to sap your energy?
Go ahead and be you,
While I try to find me,
As I'm searching for someone to be.

How now, Mr. Cumulus Cloud,
Could you please teach me how to fly?
I've come to find that gravity
Was never any good for me,
And I need to live in the sky.
Oh, Mr. Cumulus cloud,
Teach me how to soar through the air,
And bid farewell to my fears,
As I kiss the stratosphere,

title: Monochrome
extra: A compilation of some of the songs I've been working on. This, my friends, is eight years of my life recorded in three hours. Some of these songs weren't actually finished until they were in the process of being recorded. Most of them were done in one take. None of them had any editing done at all. All in all, it's rough, it's unpolished, it's remarkably bare...but the journey has to begin somewhere.

Rick Gardner’s musical journey has been a very strange ride. Bustin Bob Mitchell, the noted Cincinnati, OH Funk Journalist, said “Gardner’s resulting “rubberhorn” sound is now emerging. This is an unfeigned and unique mix of latin-influenced rhythms, ambient textures, raw funk grooves, techno and neo-jazz interposing. All flawlessly interpreted by this master player with over 40 exhilarating years of veteran experience in his chops”. P-Funk radio’s JTRP aka Keith Jackson recently said “Your music is like a movie sound track….sounds like something’s about to happen!”
Rick has spent the last few years developing a music production studio for the purpose of licensing his music through various online sources.
For over 40 years he toured the world with Bill Chase, Marvin Gaye, Bootsy Collins, and George Clinton. Fred Wesley, Maceo Parker, Kush Griffith and Rick were the world famous “Horny Horns”. He played electric trumpet with Ray “Doors” Manzarek at the Whiskey A Go Go with guest artist Iggy Pop. In July of 2002 he performed at the ESPY Awards show with Snoop Dogg and Bootsy Collins hosted by Samuel L Jackson. He is on the Brian Culbertson CD “Bringing Back the Funk”. One of his co-written works, Lickety Split aired on Saturday Night Live. He has received several RIAA awards.
"Who would have thought that somebody coming out of Wichita would have done things with these kind of people.” THE WICHITA EAGLE by Kevin Sheedy Sunday, September 17, 2000 Section: ARTS & LEISURE Edition: main page: 1D You can find more information about Rick or listen to his music at http://www.rubberhorn.com

extra: The singer song writer/Producer/formally known as Carlos Guerreiro born in the sunny state of Algarve Portugal,Carlos moved to Australia in 1969.  He played in cover bands in the 1980`s and created his own music on the Side with intention to create his own original band. In 1995 he started to produce some of his creations at Excalibur productions Working together with EMI, Producer songwriters, Hayden bell & Oliver Jones { Older brother of Savage Garden } and other producers such as Duncan Wood from {Touchwood productions } In 2010 he was recognised as a Professional Nashville writer & signed on songwriters contract to Paramount Song .com and was sent an Itunes & Amazons None exclusive record contract through { Startune records }

This was written entirely with Chris (he's singing, and again the production was split between us), from scratch, in the space of about 12 hours today. It will feature on the album-length project we intend to release together.

If this doesn't get your head nodding I'll be disappointed. Share this shit and download the hell out of it.

A big old dirty thanks goes to Ivan Brajkovic for guiding me as I mixed this thing. Thank you sir!

title: It's Already Happened Before
extra: Single off the upcoming debut album "A Good Place To Start".

After attending a Miles Davis concert, he was swept into the jazz scene of the 70s. Though originally from Ohio, it was in Miami where he met bassist, Mark Egan (Pat Metheny Band) and drummer Stu Nevitt of Shadowfax, along with many other great players. "Most importantly, I took bass and arrangement lessons from a "then unknown" Jaco Pastorius. I also spent many evenings in local clubs listening to saxophonist, Ira Sullivan, who inspired me to later play sax." Jack returned to Ohio and joined THE SOURCE. This alternative rock band put 2 EPs in the top 20 of the CMJ National college charts. THE SOURCE was part of the Akron Sound that included heavy weights Devo and Chrissy Hynde. When THE SOURCE broke up in 1986, Jack packed up and headed west to California. He settled first in San Francisco. "It was at this time that I made a conscious shift from bass guitar to saxophone. Improvisation was key to the sound I was striving for." His next band, IN THE POCKET! was a jazz fusion band that allowed Jack to continue experimenting with blending sounds. It was a short lived project, but the band's album, LADIES AND GENTLEMEN PRESENTING IN THE POCKET! was nominated for consideration by the Grammy® committee. Jack presently resides in Oakland, CA. "This city IS a musical hub. I have my own studio, and have released 4 CD's on my own record label, as well as writing/recording the soundtrack music for 4 independent movies. Most recently, I had a song placed in the internationally released global warming documentary entitled,"COOL IT". I supply the sax and bass, as well as the midi keyboards, production and engineering on most of my tracks.I blend samples, loops, special effects and assorted rhythms with the ever present improvisational spirit of jazz. My songs range from Jazz, Jazz Fusion, and Jazz Electronica, to Reggae, Rock and Clasical.” Having my own studio allows me to quickly turn projects around for clients. I feel a bit like a mad scientist in his lab as I try to push the envelope of these tunes, but what a good time!"

title: Friends Forever
extra:
My best friend is an acquaintance, eleven years but he don’t care,
I’m out of time and losing patience, for a boy who won’t learn to share,
I guess I’m not good enough for your beer and your bags of weed,
Well never mind, I’ve got the good stuff,
Sitting here alone with me.

Why bother when you don’t care,
I’d rather destroy my life than hear,
Your lack of interest in me,
Why bother, I’d rather fall asleep.

My girlfriend doesn’t know me, she only pretends to care,
She’s out of lies and losing focus on a boy who’s just playing fair,
I guess I’m not cool enough, even with my punk rock band,
Well don’t you mind, I’m not afraid of love,
Though it falls through my hands like sand.

I’d rather fall asleep,
Back at home, back in bed, where I’ll masturbate instead,
Fight my thoughts, fuck my head, contemplate the things you said,
Why bother when you don’t care,
Best friends they come so rare.

Why bother when I don’t care,
And I’d rather get destroyed and disappear,
I have no interest in me,
Why bother when I’m so fucking weird.

title: Country
extra:
If you ask Chelbie who her biggest musical influences are, don’t be surprised when she answers, “God, Reba, and Willie Nelson.” From the time she donned her first pair of red fringe boots, Chelbie was a star. Singing into hairbrushes, karaoke machines, and fireplaces just to hear her voice echo, Chelbie’s versions of “Fancy” and “Walkin’ After Midnight” quickly became family favorites. Her performances at church revivals and bluegrass festivals helped to develop her love of gospel and bluegrass, but it was her performances at opry houses across North Texas that gave her the first true taste of the thrill of being onstage.

Chelbie has performed at the famed Johnnie High’s Country Music Revue in Arlington, which has served as a career catalyst for many successful artists including LeAnn Rimes, Steve Holy, Lee Ann Womack, John Anderson, and more. She has also been a featured performer at venues such as The Cotton Pickin’ Theatre in Pointe, Texas where she was a finalist in the “Rural American Idol” competition as well as hostess of the “Saturday Nite Shindig Show.” Her other on-stage appearances include the Mt Pleasant Jamboree, the Hopkins County Fall Festival Gospel Songfest, and the Catalpa Festival in Scroggins, Texas.

Trained on the violin, piano, guitar, mandolin, and harmonica, Chelbie's love of music spans past the stage. However, songwriting has always been her true passion. Discovering her talent at an early age, Chelbie’s original music has won multiple awards including first place in the Americana Music Festival songwriting competition which earned her a single-song publishing contract for her Christmas tune, “Home for the Holidays.” She also received two honorable mention awards in the Diamond Rio Nashville Song Search for her songs “You’ll Still Be Gone” and the fan favorite “Not Love Me Anymore,” which is featured on her new album. Most recently, Chelbie’s piano ballad, “Compete With You,” was selected by the licensing company Song and Film for placement on a major cable TV network. More details about the song placement will be coming soon.
I'm a songwriter/producer from Newcastle upon Tyne in England. I've had songs published in the UK and am currently looking for publishing deals/song placements in the RnB/Pop genres.

title: My Life in Pictures (Tara Version)
extra:
Hey there... I'm Glenn and I'm a songwriter from New Jersey. Some people say my songs stink, to which I say, "Oh yeah??? What do you know about music, Paul McCartney??" Sheesh. A guy writes some of the most beloved songs of our time and suddenly he thinks he's an EXPERT or something! Well, I say let's show "the cute one" what real music is by supporting my songs! YAY! Or... not. Seriously though, I hope you like what you hear, and thanks for your time. Sincerely, Glenn


About "My Life in Pictures":

Hey everyone - thanks for checking out my latest single, "My Life in Pictures." I'm endlessly inspired by the topics of memory and loss, and the basic idea for this song stemmed from, of all things, a friend's digital picture frame (the kind that changes the image every few seconds).

It made me think of the ways we try to freeze moments in our lives and hold onto them and keep them alive in the present, even when they're no longer an accurate representation of the past.

It also made me think about, with the advent of things like youtube, the ways we are documenting more and more of our pasts almost to the point where the past and present are existing simultaneously. Of course, if you spend your present living in the past, what will you look back on in the future when you think about today?

I'm very proud of this song, and I hope you enjoy it as well.

Thanks, Glenn Page 4/9/12

Passionate, heartfelt, soulful, and real. Amanda Jo's music will touch your heart, inspire you, make you laugh, and will leave you wanting to hear more.

Amanda Jo is a naturally-born country music singer andsong writer. By the age of 2, Amanda began to entertain by singing on top of the picnic tables and would begin to draw a crowd. At the age of six, she performed for the first time on a stage at a county fair in Minnesota. By age eleven, Amanda was hired as a performer with The Minnesota Opera Company.

Eventually, Amanda found her musical passion in the Country music genre after hearing LeAnn Rimes rendition of “Blue”. She has performed at various renowned venues including The Target Center, Whisky a Go Go and The Ordway Center.

Amanda relocated to Nashville in November 2012 and has been performing for audiences all over Music City. She performs music from Loretta Lynn to Miranda Lambert and everything in between, in addition to her own original music.

title: Peace of Mind
extra:
Steve Major, is a young artist hailing from Canada. With the release of his new album 'UNDOING', Major hopes to hit new heights with his already well rounded and budding career in the entertainment industry. He has been entertaining audiences of all ages for over 18 years. He is a diverse performer with a resume that covers starring roles in musical theatre, roles in film and commercials, an international album release through DEP/Universal Music, and hosting Canada's very own reality television series / original music competition "LOCAL LIVE CANADA™". "Writing music, recording it, and then having the chance to get up onstage and share it with people is something I've always loved to do. This new album (solo album) is something that I've been wanting to do for a long time,” said Major, who is no stranger to the recording studio. His first recording gig in '98 which was a product of Sony Music Canada was a children s album. Other projects soon followed including an international album release through DEP/Universal Music for the duo 'ST.Eves', which Major attributes to being the turning point in his recording journey. “I really felt it was time to do my own thing. I've been in a group setting, I've done the band thing, but now I'm honestly ready to do it on my own. Who know's, maybe one day ST.Eves will fly again", Major added.

To create "UNDOING", Major worked with several pro musicians from Toronto, as well as upcoming producer Jazzfeezy who recently finished working on the latest single from T.I titled "I Ain't Goin". All tracks were recorded by Jim Zoils at the Rose Room Studio in Downtown Toronto, Canada. The album was mixed and had additional production done by gold and mulit-platinum award winning Producer/Mixer Michael Jack who has worked with some of the greats including Nelly Furtado and Bono from U2. Major started working on "UNDOING" in 2011 and relates every song to a specific situation that has taken place in his life. The pop/rock nine song album is mostly up-tempo and houses two ballads. “My inspiration for the overall sound of this record comes from growing up listening to Michael Jackson and Justin Timberlake. I wanted the music to be catchy, dance-able, but carry a message that all could relate to.” Major's new album "UNDOING" is now available on iTunes worldwide among other online music retailers.

Steve has been seen on stage in various theatrical roles including ROGER in "RENT" and as JOSEPH in "JOSEPH AND THE AMAZING TECHNICOLOR DREAMCOAT". Other theatrical credits include: "Anything Goes", "Sweet Charity", "Oliver", "The Sound of Music", and "Brigadoon" to name a few.

Steve has rocked stages all over Canada and has performed many times internationally. His desire to sing has led him to many stages including the Dominican Republic, New York City, Las Vegas, and to a feature performance locally in Canada for promotion of CTV's Canadian Idol at the Air Canada Center. Steve’s studio recording credits include "Groove Club: Canadian Kids &Friends" with Sony Music, "ST.Eves: All That I Need" with DEP/Universal Music, "Leaving you Behind", a collaboration single with Canadian Rap Artist PHAX off of Jazzfeezy's debut album 'Jazzfezzy presents: Unveiling the Rapture', two singles - from 2011- "Checkmate!" and 2012 - "Piece of Mind". Major released "Undoing" in 2015.
